{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Make Instance Transform"], "type": "title", "extent": [85, 113], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [113, 210], "text": ["Builds a general 4\u00d74 transform matrix derived from the\nstandard copy/instance attributes"]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [210, 531], "text": ["This operator builds a general 4\u00d74 transform matrix from a set of input parameters\nthat match the attributes and priorities used in ", {"text": ["Copy and Instancing\noperations "], "fullpath": "/copy/instanceattrs", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/copy/instanceattrs"}, ".  Those inputs that can take precedence over others\nwill also have a corresponding ", {"text": ["use"], "type": "code"}, " input to signify their value should be used."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [531, 925], "text": ["For example, create a ", {"text": ["Parameter VOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/parameter", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/parameter"}, " bound to the ", {"text": ["orient"], "type": "code"}, " attribute, plug its output into the ", {"text": ["orient"], "type": "code"}, " input of this VOP, and plug its ", {"text": ["bound_orient"], "type": "code"}, " output into the\n", {"text": ["useorient"], "type": "code"}, " input.  The VOP will use the value from the ", {"text": ["orient"], "type": "code"}, " parameter when it is\nbound to an attribute on the geometry, but use lower precedence attributes like\n", {"text": ["N"], "type": "code"}, " or ", {"text": ["v"], "type": "code"}, " if no such attribute exists."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [934, 958], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/makexform", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/makexform"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [958, 986], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/transformspace", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/v